## Overview

Implement complete image support in Notes to achieve visual note-taking parity with Obsidian/Notion. This is THE critical gap preventing Notes from being a true "second brain" tool.

**Impact:**
- **User Value:** CRITICAL - Visual thinking, screenshots, diagrams, photos
- **Marketing:** Unblocks "second brain" positioning
- **Competition:** Moves Notes from 50% → 65% Obsidian parity
- **Bundle Size:** +5KB (Lexical ImagePlugin is tree-shakeable)

---

## Problem Statement

**Current State:**
- Notes support rich text (headings, lists, tables, code)
- NO image support (paste image = nothing happens)
- Users expect visual note-taking (screenshots, diagrams, photos)

**User Pain:**
- Cannot paste screenshots from clipboard
- Cannot drag-drop images into notes
- Cannot take photos on mobile
- Cannot create visual documentation

**Competitive Gap:**
- Obsidian: Full image support (embed, resize, alt text)
- Notion: Full image support (upload, paste, drag-drop, resize)
- Neuman Brain: ❌ NO IMAGE SUPPORT

